body:
## Description
The following solidity code:
```solidity
import "hardhat/console.sol";
pragma solidity ^0.8.17;
contract test {
    constructor() {
        console.log(0);
    }
}
```
Doesn't work in remix and the following code is shown in the development console:
```JS
Uncaught (in promise) Error: invalid function signature (argument="value", value="logundefined view", code=INVALID_ARGUMENT, version=abi/5.5.0)
    at lib_esm_Logger.makeError (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:153:13)
    at lib_esm_Logger.throwError (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:154:44)
    at lib_esm_Logger.throwArgumentError (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:155:52)
    at FunctionFragment.fromString (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:1552:58)
    at Fragment.fromString (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:1489:67)
    at Fragment.from (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:1483:46)
    at main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:3818:172
    at Array.map (<anonymous>)
    at new Interface (main.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:3818:103)
    at VmProxy.<anonymous> (app.0.27.0.1665065785599.js:2288:822)
```
## Reproduce

You might have to "Reset to default settings" and/or remove all `.deps / npm` `console.log` versions in the file explorer to be able to reproduce.

## What is causing this?

This is related to a recent change in console.log:
From (version 2.10.1):
```solidity
function logInt(int p0) internal view {
    _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(int)", p0));
}
```

To (Version 2.10.2):
```solidity
function logInt(int256 p0) internal view {
    _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(int256)", p0));
}
```
Also see https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/issues/2589

## Workaround

As a workaround you can use an older version of `console.sol`:
```solidity
import "hardhat@2.10.1/console.sol";
pragma solidity ^0.8.17;
contract test {
    constructor() {
        console.log(0);
    }
}
```
